Method 1 — PivotTo (Best + Most Stable)

This moves the entire vehicle model cleanly. Usually the best method.

local player = game.Players.LocalPlayer
local vehicleId = player:GetAttribute("spawnedVehicleid")

local car = workspace.Vehicles:FindFirstChild(vehicleId)

if car then
	local root = car.PrimaryPart or car:FindFirstChildWhichIsA("BasePart")
	if root then
		local forward = root.CFrame.LookVector * 50
		car:PivotTo(car:GetPivot() + forward)
	end
end

✅ works with most cars
✅ moves the full vehicle
✅ low lag

Method 2 — MoveTo (Simple Teleport)

Very simple and sometimes bypasses weird physics.

local player = game.Players.LocalPlayer
local vehicleId = player:GetAttribute("spawnedVehicleid")

local car = workspace.Vehicles:FindFirstChild(vehicleId)

if car then
	local root = car.PrimaryPart or car:FindFirstChildWhichIsA("BasePart")
	if root then
		local pos = root.Position + root.CFrame.LookVector * 50
		car:MoveTo(pos)
	end
end

✅ super simple
⚠ sometimes rotates the car weird

Method 3 — Velocity Boost (Fast Dash)

Instead of teleporting it launches the car forward.

local player = game.Players.LocalPlayer
local vehicleId = player:GetAttribute("spawnedVehicleid")

local car = workspace.Vehicles:FindFirstChild(vehicleId)

if car then
	local root = car.PrimaryPart or car:FindFirstChildWhichIsA("BasePart")
	if root then
		root.AssemblyLinearVelocity = root.CFrame.LookVector * 200
	end
end

🚗 makes the car dash forward

Method 4 — Direct CFrame Teleport (Instant)

Most brute-force method.

local player = game.Players.LocalPlayer
local vehicleId = player:GetAttribute("spawnedVehicleid")

local car = workspace.Vehicles:FindFirstChild(vehicleId)

if car then
	local root = car.PrimaryPart or car:FindFirstChildWhichIsA("BasePart")
	if root then
		root.CFrame = root.CFrame + root.CFrame.LookVector * 50
	end
end

⚡ instant teleport
⚠ can fight physics sometimes
